track_notes: Leave Gwastadnant and follow obvious path up until just short of Llyn y Cwn.  Steep an and rocky in a few places. If you reach the lake you have gone just a little too far, but no harm done.  Turn left up hill and again follow the obvious path to the summit.

Link between Y Garn and Elidir Fawr to allow both to be activated on one expedition. Descend north from Y Garn.  When the descent finally flattens out at the Col before Foel Goch, make sure you keep left at this point to traverse around the west side of Foel Goch. Continue to the low point between the two mountains and then follow the obvious path up to the summit ridge of Elidir Fawr, steep in places.
For track details text see my track for GW/NW-003

Total time (including ops): 6h 15m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T5 / Grade 2 Scramble. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards.
